category: MAKE THE PHRASE
category comment: 

clue: A boxer trying to get down to, say, 135 or 175 pounds for a fight is attempting to "make" this

response: weight

clue: To discern, to complete writing a check or to engage in kissing, you "make" this

response: out

clue: To act with speed, you "make" this, also said to make waste

response: haste

clue: An attempt that'll end in success or utter disaster is described in the rhyming phrase "make or..."

response: break

clue: Something that serves as a substitute, especially of an expedient nature, is "make-" this

response: do

